        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Ménétrier disease (MD) is a rare premalignant hyperproliferative gastropathy characterized by massive overgrowth of foveolar cells in the gastric lining resulting in large gastric folds and manifesting with epigastric pain nausea vomiting peripheral edema and less commonly anorexia and weight loss."
        },
